How to reproduce:
1. Create data buffer with size more than 32Mb;
2. Write this buffer to the file using QFile::write;

expected result: written size will be equal to the buffer size;
actual result: written size is equal to std::ceil(data size / 32Mb) * 32Mb;

the reason is the next bug in the source code:
qfsfileengine_win.cpp: line 434
{code}
        if (!WriteFile(fileHandle, data + totalWritten, blockSize, &bytesWritten, NULL)) {
{code}
blockSize is constant during the write cycle, so if we writing 45Mb of data - at the second write cycle we will write not 64 - 45 = 19Mb but 32MB .

Code to reproduce:
{code}
const qint64 dataSize = 45 * 1024 * 1024;
QByteArray data(dataSize, '\0');
QFile file(FILE_NAME);
if(file.open(QFile::WriteOnly | QFile::Truncate))
{
    qint64 written = file.write(data);
    //here written will be equeal to 64 Mb
    bool success = (written == dataSize);
}
{code}

