fitViewportToGeoShape currently uses

{code:java}
    QDoubleVector2D topLeftPoint =
            m_map->referenceCoordinateToItemPosition(topLeft);
    QDoubleVector2D bottomRightPoint =
            m_map->referenceCoordinateToItemPosition(bottomRight);

    // find center of the bounding box
    QGeoCoordinate centerCoordinate =
            m_map->referenceItemPositionToCoordinate(
                (topLeftPoint + bottomRightPoint)/2);
{code}

to find the map center necessary to fit to the geoshape.
However, (topLeftPoint + bottomRightPoint)/2 would be 0 for, say, a circle centered at (0.0, -180.0), as referenceCoordinateToItemPosition and referenceItemPositionToCoordinate do not take into account the camera position and the necessary wrapping.
This incidentally works with QGeoCircle, because these corners are modified to exceed 0 or 180, but fails with QGeoRectangle

