Currently demobrowser history view does not sort items by timetamps. History items should be sorted by timestamps in history view as they are updated.

Copying [~alexandru.croitor]'s comment from https://codereview.qt-project.org/#/c/144414/4//ALL :

{quote}
Tested this locally, and it doesn't seem that visiting a previously visited link updates the position in the history, for it to be placed at the front (as Chromium does it for example), so updating the history item (and thus the date) doesn't seem to do anything in this case.
Also Chromium does this only for a certain time threshold (say if the link was visited less than an hour ago, it will be placed at the front, but if the link was visited yesterday, it will create a duplicate in the front, and leave yesterday's link in place). Not sure if we want to implement this or not, just an observation.
{quote}

